    "faqs": [
      {
        "question": "Is MRI Peripheral Angio painful?",
        "answer": "No. You may feel a cool sensation during contrast injection—that’s it.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "How soon can I resume normal activities?",
        "answer": "Immediately. We only advise 10 minutes of post-scan hydration."
      },
      {
        "question": "Will I need a driver after the scan?",
        "answer": "Not unless you take sedation. Most patients drive themselves.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What if I have kidney issues?",
        "answer": "Our team reviews your latest eGFR. Non-contrast MRA is available.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I eat before the scan?",
        "answer": "For contrast studies, a light 4-hour fast is ideal; plain water is allowed.\n"
      },
      {
        "question": "What happens after my MRI Peripheral Angio?",
        "answer": "Unless you received sedation, you can resume normal activities and diet immediately after your **MRI Peripheral Angio**. There is no specific recovery time. If contrast is used, it is eliminated naturally through the kidneys. Attend your follow-up appointment with your referring doctor to discuss the scan results and determine next steps in your care plan."
      }
    ],
